{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592401","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592401"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:13:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:13:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15230"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15230","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15230"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.87,0,0.06,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7921"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65135"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7921","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7921"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15230"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50571"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"385"},{"type":"tags","id":"1449"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5364"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19297"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19300"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21641"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65135","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65135"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe aim of colorectal cancer screening programmes is to detect cancer at an early stage, with a view to improving outcomes. Various screening methods are available and these include faecal occult blood testing, flexible sigmoidoscopy and colonoscopy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EColonoscopy could be considered the preferred screening tool.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following would be its key advantage??","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["High patient acceptance","High specificity","Low financial cost","Minimal procedural risk","Quick procedure time"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EColonoscopy is considered the gold standard for colorectal cancer screening due to its excellent diagnostic accuracy. It has both \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigh specificity\u003C/strong\u003E (few false positives) and high sensitivity for detecting cancer and precancerous polyps.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, colonoscopy has several disadvantages. It is not a \u003Cstrong\u003Elow financial cost\u003C/strong\u003E screening test due to the equipment, facilities and skilled staff required. Colonoscopy is not at \u003Cstrong\u003Eminimal procedural risk\u003C/strong\u003E as complications can include bleeding, perforation and adverse reactions to sedation. It is not a \u003Cstrong\u003Equick procedure\u003C/strong\u003E as it requires bowel preparation, the procedure itself and recovery time.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key advantages of colonoscopy include direct visualisation of the entire colon, ability to take biopsies, and removal of polyps during the same procedure. The high specificity means that when a lesion is identified as suspicious, it is very likely to be significant rather than a false positive finding.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EColonoscopy does not have \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigh patient acceptance\u003C/strong\u003E due to the invasive nature of the procedure, the need for bowel preparation, and potential discomfort or anxiety associated with the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Colonoscopy has high sensitivity and specificity for detecting colorectal cancer and precancerous polyps.","Colonoscopy is an invasive, expensive screening test with small but significant procedural risks.","Colonoscopy allows for direct visualisation and immediate biopsy/removal of suspicious lesions."],"references":["Shaukat A, Levin TR. Current and future colorectal cancer screening strategies. Nat Rev Gastroenterol Hepatol. 2022 Aug;19(8):521-531. doi: 10.1038/s41575-022-00612-y. Epub 2022 May 3. Erratum in: Nat Rev Gastroenterol Hepatol. 2022 Aug;19(8):551. doi: 10.1038/s41575-022-00661-3. PMID: 35505243; PMCID: PMC9063618.","Kumar R, Lewis CR. Colon Cancer Screening. [Updated 2024 Sep 10]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK559064/","Lin JS, Perdue LA, Henrikson NB, Bean SI, Blasi PR. Screening for Colorectal Cancer: Updated Evidence Report and Systematic Review for the US Preventive Services Task Force. JAMA. 2021 May 18;325(19):1978-1998. doi: 10.1001/jama.2021.4417. Erratum in: JAMA. 2021 Jul 20;326(3):279. doi: 10.1001/jama.2021.10417. PMID: 34003220","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50571"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15230"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50571","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50571"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T14:54:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T14:55:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7921"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65135"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group